We are looking for a Data Scientist who can turn complex data into scalable analytical solutions, drive predictive insights and enhance service performance across the organization.




Responsibilities:

Design, develop, and implement analytical services and data-based solutions using Dataiku;
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand business needs and provide service-oriented analytical support;
Manipulate and analyze complex, high-volume and high-dimensional data from various sources;
Implement predictive models and machine learning algorithms, monitoring their performance and optimizing them to support services;
Translate data insights into actionable recommendations and present results to stakeholders to enhance services;
Maintain and improve existing DSS Dataiku projects, ensuring service continuity;
Stay up to date with the latest trends and technologies in data science and machine learning to improve service quality.




Required Skills:

Experience with Big Data technologies (Hadoop, Spark, GCP, etc.);
Knowledge of platforms and analytical solutions focused on services;
DSS Dataiku certification (a plus) ;
Strong understanding of predictive modeling, machine learning, and data mining concepts;
Proficiency in Python or R, with experience in SQL;
Excellent analytical, problem-solving, and communication skills;
Ability to work in a dynamic, team-oriented environment focused on service delivery.




Be part of a team that turns data into real service innovation—apply now.

